summary: one thing hp fanfiction really needs to stop doing is following jk rowling’s example when it comes to fat-shaming the ‘bad-guy’...
body:
one thing hp fanfiction really needs to stop doing is following jk rowling’s example when it comes to fat-shaming

the ‘bad-guy’ characters are fat cows, pigs, and toads

meanwhile the only overweight ‘good’ characters get to have just a bit of chub (neville) or motherly rolls (molly). or if it’s a sort of grey character he’s got the belly of a jolly old man (slughorn, mundungus).

it’s like a kick to my plus-sized gut every time I see the dursleys or umbridge hated on because they’re fat. there are plenty of other reasons to hate them. their weight shouldn’t factor into whether they’re a good or likable person.

fanfic writers like to celebrate themselves for fixing jkr’s work, but this is one thing that’s stuck around and no one thinks it needs to be fixed

summary: Sirius: Why do people think bisexuality is confusing? It’s not. You know what is confusing? Bi-annual. Does it mean every two...
body:
Sirius: Why do people think bisexuality is confusing? It’s not. You know what is confusing? Bi-annual. Does it mean every two years or twice a year? No one knows.
Remus: Bi-annual means twice a year! Biennial means every other year!
Lily: Actually, biennial means every other year, semiannual means twice a year.
Lily: You wanna know what bi-annual means?
Sirius: It means you should hate the English language.
